verbose_text: Interestingly, PC specific elevation of ROS levels also caused an abnormal heart rhythm, similar to that observed following PC specific reduction of ROS levels; namely, increased frequency of irregular beats, broader distribution of HPs, and significantly increased the AI (XREF_FIG, XREF_SUPPLEMENTARY) compared with wild-type and control hearts (XREF_FIG, XREF_SUPPLEMENTARY).
